  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Response to cholera outbreak in Borno, Yobe and Adamawa States, North East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this UNICEF project is to contain and stop the cholera transmission in the affected areas in Nigeria. With thsi CERF grant, UNICEF will repair 86 water facilities, will procure and distribute 3,000 WASH kits, and will print and distribute 20,000 IEC materials on the prevention of cholera. The project will last six months and will benefit 134,000 persons including 72,360 women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
